  <reviews>
    <item index="0">
      <text>One of the few directors who can play a multi-sword evisceration for laughs, Miike has served up another frenetic joy.</text>
      <source>Time Out</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>https://www.timeout.com/london/film/blade-of-the-immortal</link>
      <author>Philip De Semlyen</author>
    </item>
    <item index="1">
      <text>Swords are drawn, guts are spilled, and so forth, but it feels as if the man who made the all-timers Ichi the Killer and Dead or Alive 2: Birds is merely going through the motions.</text>
      <source>Globe and Mail</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/film/film-reviews/review-blade-of-the-immortal-merely-goes-through-the-motions/article37001392/</link>
      <author>Barry Hertz</author>
    </item>
    <item index="2">
      <text>It is being touted as "Miike's 100th film" and, while one could argue whether the numbering is strictly correct, it's close enough to be reasonable. Here's to another 100.</text>
      <source>ReelViews</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.reelviews.net/reelviews/blade-of-the-immortal</link>
      <author>James Berardinelli</author>
    </item>
    <item index="3">
      <text>It's that balance of Miike's experience with his retained childlike energy in making a kick-ass samurai movie that keeps this journey engaging.</text>
      <source>RogerEbert.com</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/blade-of-the-immortal-2017</link>
      <author>Brian Tallerico</author>
    </item>
    <item index="4">
      <text>The director's 100th feature, Blade of the Immortal shows Miike to have lost none of the madcap energy and wit that characterize his best work. And while this is not that, it's still got more style to burn than almost any recent Hollywood actioner.</text>
      <source>Hollywood Reporter</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/blade-immortal-review-1005100</link>
      <author>Harry Windsor</author>
    </item>
    <item index="5">
      <text>Miike retains his twisted sense of humor, with mangling and disemboweling deployed for comic effect. And after 99 movies, he certainly knows how to make action memorable.</text>
      <source>Los Angeles Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://beta.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-capsule-blade-of-the-immortal-review-20171102-story.html</link>
      <author>Noel Murray</author>
    </item>
    <item index="6">
      <text>Marvel Studios probably won't be hiring Takashi Miike to direct his take on any of its properties any time soon. But Blade Of The Immortal makes that seem like an exciting idea.</text>
      <source>AV Club</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>https://www.avclub.com/takashi-miike-rings-in-100-movies-with-the-garish-gory-1820061335</link>
      <author>Katie Rife</author>
    </item>
    <item index="7">
      <text>"Blade" goes for the carotid while offering a classic look and a comic-book story. It's part Kurosawa, part "X-Men," part "Ichi the Killer."</text>
      <source>Washington Post</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/blade-of-the-immortal-samurai-is-cursed-with-eternal-life--and-seemingly-interminable-sword-fights/2017/11/02/e35ed64c-b9bb-11e7-be94-fabb0f1e9ffb_story.html?utm_term=.644a8f179595</link>
      <author>Mark Jenkins</author>
    </item>
    <item index="8">
      <text>Not often do you encounter a movie about slicing, dicing samurai vivisecting each other into gory chunks that is also a thing of beauty.</text>
      <source>Minneapolis Star Tribune</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.startribune.com/blade-of-the-immortal-is-clearly-a-cut-above/454712633/</link>
      <author>Colin Covert</author>
    </item>
    <item index="9">
      <text>Though not nearly as mindful or meaty as Mr. Miike's 2011 triumph, "13 Assassins," "Blade" is creatively gory fun.</text>
      <source>New York Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/02/movies/blade-of-the-immortal-review-takashi-miike.html</link>
      <author>Jeannette Catsoulis</author>
    </item>
    <item index="10">
      <text>How does a good director like Takashi misfire so badly?</text>
      <source>San Francisco Chronicle</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.sfchronicle.com/movies/article/Blade-of-the-Immortal-is-death-by-a-12325084.php</link>
      <author>G. Allen Johnson</author>
    </item>
    <item index="11">
      <text>Come for the gory swordplay, stay for the half-serious melodrama.</text>
      <source>Village Voice</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>https://www.villagevoice.com/2017/11/01/takashi-miikes-blade-of-the-immortal-will-take-your-breath-away/</link>
      <author>Simon Abrams</author>
    </item>
    <item index="12">
      <text>Blade of the Immortal is flat-out gorgeous.</text>
      <source>Philadelphia Inquirer</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/blade-of-the-immortal-takashi-miike-review-20171101.html</link>
      <author>Gary Thompson</author>
    </item>
    <item index="13">
      <text>What I daresay is the most violent samurai epic ever struck off by the hand of man.</text>
      <source>Seattle Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>https://www.seattletimes.com/entertainment/movies/blade-of-the-immortal-vengeance-drives-violence-in-takashi-miikes-latest/?utm_source=RSS&amp;utm_medium=Referral&amp;utm_campaign=RSS_movies</link>
      <author>Soren Anderson</author>
    </item>
    <item index="14">
      <text>The 100th feature by genre master Takashi Miike transcends conventions of Japanese swordplay films with both fantasy and graphic violence.</text>
      <source>Variety</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/blade-of-the-immortal-review-1202431125/</link>
      <author>Maggie Lee</author>
    </item>
    <item index="15">
      <text>One of Takashi Miike's most lethal works.</text>
      <source>indieWire</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.indiewire.com/2017/05/blade-of-the-immortal-review-takashi-miike-cannes-1201828147/</link>
      <author>Ben Croll</author>
    </item>
    <item index="16">
      <text>Further proof that of all the genres he dabbles in, samurai cinema is the one that brings out the grandest entertainer in Miike. Here's to 100 more.</text>
      <source>AV Club</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.avclub.com/live/cannes-opens-once-latest-master-director-255483/entry/822</link>
      <author>A.A. Dowd</author>
    </item>
  </reviews>
